  "executive_brief_md": "## TIGIT \u2014 T cell immunoreceptor with Ig and ITIM domains\n\n**White Space score 20.85/100 \u00b7 rank 10/13 \u00b7 HIGH confidence.** Mid-cohort \u2014 real biology with moderate competition; watch the momentum trend.\n\nTIGIT is a cell membrane ; single-pass type i membrane protein target in the immuno-oncology cohort with no approved drug yet. Development level **Tchem**; mechanism: T-cell immunoreceptor with Ig and ITIM domains antagonist; T-cell immunoreceptor with Ig and ITIM domains inhibitor. Competitive footprint: 10 industry sponsor(s) in trials. Leading disease associations: non-small cell lung carcinoma, small cell lung carcinoma, esophageal squamous cell carcinoma, neurodegenerative disease.\n\n**Score decomposition** \u2014 Validation 0.4233, Tractability 0.9, Saturation 0.4526 (cohort-normalized). The score is multiplicative, so crowding drives it down even when biology is validated \u2014 which is why saturated checkpoints sit low and validated-but-uncrowded targets rise.\n\n*Every figure above resolves to a versioned source in the Provenance tab. This brief is model-written (claude-fable-5) over sourced facts only.*",
